thread.title: Girls tennis: Nine Indians qualify for conference tourney
thread.title_full: Girls tennis: Nine Indians qualify for conference tourney

author: J.B. Cozens
title: Girls tennis: Nine Indians qualify for conference tourney
text:
By J.B. Cozens on October 13,   
The John Jay girls tennis team is hosting the Conference I tournament for the first time this week, starting today at 3 on the new courts on the John Jay campus. 
The Indians, coming off an 11-0 regular season, have nine of 11 starting players qualified for the tourney, which concludes on Friday. They have more players in the tourney than any other team in the 21-school conference. 
Top singles player Anya Ivenitsky is seeded second in the singles draw, while the Indians’ other two singles players, Bailey Burke and Tatiana Blechman, are joining forces to play doubles. 
Three other doubles teams also qualified — Izzy Bienen and Sonia Lange, Callie Sacks and Acadia Thielking, and Nadia Shtohryn and Lily Gengler. 
“It’s going to be exciting,” said Coach Mike Racanelli. “Anya has a real good chance of making sectionals, and hopefully a few of the doubles teams do, too.” 
Caitlyn Ferrante of Yorktown is the top seed in the singles bracket. 
The tournament features 16 singles players and 20 doubles teams. 
Five singles players and five doubles teams from each of the three conference tournaments will qualify for the Section 1 tournament, which starts next Tuesday at Harrison High School. Izzy Bienen plays a ball at the net during the first doubles matches of the John Jay girls tennis team’s win over Somers last Saturday at home. — J.B. Cozens photo Related posts:
